King Salman bin Abdulaziz al-Saud of Saudi Arabia called President Obama to express his regret at not being able to travel to Washington. Instead, he confirmed that Crown Prince Mohammed bin Nayef and Deputy Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman would be representing the Kingdom. The President and King Salman discussed the agenda for the upcoming meetings and agreed on the importance of working closely with other GCC member states to address regional threats and conflicts. They also talked about the need for a comprehensive agreement between the P5+1 and Iran regarding Iran's nuclear program. The President welcomed Saudi Arabia's announcement of a cease-fire and humanitarian pause in Yemen and both leaders agreed on the urgency of addressing the humanitarian situation in the country. They highlighted the strength of the partnership between the two countries and their commitment to the stability and prosperity of the region. They also agreed to continue close consultations on various issues.